      <hedline>
        <hl1>A World of Immigrants</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ewart Stuger says immigrants to Ireland from Africa and other European countries will add to cultural mix, just as the Irish did for other countries (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Irish Now Face the Other Side of Immigration'' (front page, July 8):</p>
        <p>The residents of the small town of Birr, Ireland, are getting a sense of what a global village the world is becoming.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Irish Now Face the Other Side of Immigration'' (front page, July 8):</p>
        <p>The residents of the small town of Birr, Ireland, are getting a sense of what a global village the world is becoming.</p>
        <p>These newcomers from Africa and Europe will undoubtedly add to the cultural mix, the same way the Irish did for other countries. Nothing is wrong with immigration seekers, as long as the process is sensible and humane.</p>
        <p>With a good cultural awareness program, the Irish have an opportunity to make a difference to the downtrodden refugees.</p>
        <p>EWART STUGER  Brooklyn, July 9, 2000</p>
      </block>
